  "prompt": "Bank Accounts: How do I know whether my bank account is linked to my Aadhaar card or not?",
  "response": "To check whether your bank account is linked to your Aadhaar card, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Online Banking Portal:**\n   - Log in to your bank's internet banking portal.\n   - Navigate to the section for linking Aadhaar or personal details.\n   - There might be an option to check the linking status of your Aadhaar card.\n\n2. **SMS Service:**\n   - Some banks offer an SMS service where you can send a message to inquire about the linking status. You need to check with your bank for the specific format and number.\n\n3. **Bank Branch Visit:**\n   - You can visit your bank's branch and ask a customer service representative to check if your Aadhaar is linked to your account. Bring along your Aadhaar card for verification.\n\n4. **Aadhaar Authentication:**\n   - Use the official UIDAI website or the mAadhaar app, where you may find options for verifying if your Aadhaar is linked to various services, including bank accounts.\n\n5. **Check Bank Statements:**\n   - Some bank statements might mention whether your Aadhaar has been linked, so reviewing recent statements may provide information.\n\n6. **Customer Care:**\n   - Call the customer service number of your bank and inquire about your Aadhaar linkage status.\n\nMake sure your contact information is updated with your bank to receive necessary notifications regarding your account status.",
